    "description": "Are you a skilled Radiologist looking for your next big career move? 3M India Healthcare Digital Technologies in Rajkot offers you the perfect platform to grow professionally and personally.\n\nAbout 3M India Healthcare Digital Technologies:\n3M India Healthcare Digital Technologies is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Respond to medical emergencies and provide immediate care\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Maintain accurate clinical documentation in electronic health records\n• Ensure patient privacy and maintain confidentiality\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Post Graduate Diploma in relevant field\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Wound Care\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in Surgical Procedures\n• Proficiency in Pharmacovigilance\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n• Proficiency in Medical Terminology\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Rajkot, Gujarat, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with 3M India Healthcare Digital Technologies!",
